**suggestion:** generateNodeIdPrefixed uses string manipulation on contentType.

Using split and join on contentType may not handle all enum cases correctly. Recommend implementing a more reliable mapping or validation to ensure consistent id formats.

Suggested implementation:

```typescript
const NODE_TYPE_PREFIX_MAP: Record<NodeType, string> = {
  [NodeType.TWEET]: "tweet",
  [NodeType.BLUESKY_POST]: "blueskypost",
  // Add other NodeType mappings here as needed
};

export function generateNodeIdPrefixed(contentType: NodeType, id: string) {
  const prefix = NODE_TYPE_PREFIX_MAP[contentType];
  if (!prefix) {
    throw new Error(`Unknown NodeType for prefix mapping: ${contentType}`);
  }
  return generateResourceId(Resource.node, {
    prefix,
    id
  });
}

```

You may need to add all relevant `NodeType` enum values to the `NODE_TYPE_PREFIX_MAP` to ensure complete coverage. If new types are added in the future, update the mapping accordingly.

